{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "ProsperStack API Reference",
    "version": "v1",
    "description": "This is the reference documentation for the ProsperStack API v1. Visit ProsperStack at [prosperstack.com](https://prosperstack.com).\n\nFor more information on ProsperStack features, see the [primary documentation](https://prosperstack.com/docs/).\n\nLet us know how we can improve the API, documentation or anything else you need help with at [support@prosperstack.com](mailto:support@prosperstack.com).\n\n# Introduction\n\nThe ProsperStack API provides a [REST](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer)-like interface to your ProsperStack data. It uses standard HTTP verbs, accepts JSON-encoded request bodies and provides JSON-encoded responses.\n\nYou can use the ProsperStack API to access your live production data or data from [test mode](https://prosperstack.com/docs/test-mode/). The API key you use to authenticate requests determines which mode will be used.\n\n# Authentication\n\nThe ProsperStack API uses API keys to authenticate requests. You can manage your API keys from the [ProsperStack API Keys settings page](https://app.prosperstack.com/settings/api-keys).\n\nLive mode API keys have the prefix `key_` and test mode API keys have the prefix `key_test_`.\n\nAuthentication uses [HTTP basic authentication](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic_access_authentication). Provide your API key as the basic authentication username. You don't need to provide a password.\n\nA simple example using cURL:\n\n```bash\ncurl https://api.prosperstack.com/v1/flow_sessions \\\n-u key_LSdJXBrN3SP7bdJrQSMp2eZK:\n```\n\n[Learn more about creating API keys.](https://prosperstack.com/docs/api/)\n\n# Pagination\n\nAll list endpoints support cursor-based pagination. The body of a list response will contain a `data` property with an array of objects and a `next_cursor` property desginating the cursor value to retrieve the next set of results.\n\nUse the value of `next_cursor` in the `cursor` query parameter to specify the set of results to return. If `next_cursor` is `null`, there are no more results.\n\nYou can also specify a `limit` in the query parameters to adjust the number of items per result set. The limit defaults to 10 and has a maximum of 100.\n\n# Rate limits\n\nThe ProsperStack API enforces a rate limit of 100 requests per minute. Your live mode and test mode accounts have separate limits.\n\nWhen the rate limit is exceeded, requests will fail with the HTTP status `429 Too Many Requests` until the limit window resets.\n\nThe ProsperStack API implements the [RateLimit Header Fields for HTTP draft](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/draft-ietf-httpapi-ratelimit-headers) which describes a set of HTTP headers you can use to observe current request limits.\n\nThe headers are:\n\n- `RateLimit-Limit` \u2014 The limit of requests per time window (1 minute)\n- `RateLimit-Remaining` \u2014 The number of requests left before exceeding the limit\n- `RateLimit-Reset` \u2014 The number of seconds until the limit window resets\n\nIf you need to exceed the rate limit, let us know at [support@prosperstack.com](mailto:support@prosperstack.com) and we'll be happy to help.\n",
    "x-logo": {
      "url": "https://prosperstack.com/images/logo-api.svg"
    },
    "x-jentic-source-url": "https://developers.prosperstack.com/openapi.json"
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "https://api.prosperstack.com/v1"
    }
  ],
  "security": [
    {
      "basicAuth": []
    }
  ],
  "tags": [
    {
      "name": "flows",
      "x-displayName": "Flows",
      "description": "A flow represents a ProsperStack cancellation flow.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "flow_sessions",
      "x-displayName": "Flow sessions",
      "description": "A flow session represents the session a cancelling subscriber took when going through the ProsperStack cancellation flow, including answers to survey questions and any offers presented or accepted.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "offers",
      "x-displayName": "Offers",
      "description": "An offer represents a [ProsperStack offer](https://docs.prosperstack.com/offers/creating-an-offer).\n\nOffers can be of type `coupon`, `pause_subscription`, `trial_extension`, `change_plan` or `custom`.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "offer-links",
      "x-displayName": "Offer links",
      "description": "An offer link is a unique URL associating a landing page offer with a particular subscription. [Learn more.](https://docs.prosperstack.com/offers/offer-links)\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "payments",
      "x-displayName": "Payments",
      "description": "A payment represents a retained payment made by a saved or deflected subscriber.\n\nPayments can be of type `saved` or `deflected`.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "properties",
      "x-displayName": "Properties",
      "description": "A property represents a [ProsperStack custom property](https://prosperstack.com/docs/custom-properties/) defined for subscribers or subscriptions.\n\nProperties can be used to store custom data with your subscribers and subscriptions. They can be of type `text`, `number`, `boolean` or `date`.\n\nEach custom property must be attached to either the `subscriber` or `subscription` entity type.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "subscribers",
      "x-displayName": "Subscribers",
      "description": "A subscriber represents a customer of your product.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "subscriptions",
      "x-displayName": "Subscriptions",
      "description": "A subscription represents a subscription belonging to a customer of your product.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "webhooks",
      "x-displayName": "Webhooks",
      "description": "A webhook represents a [ProsperStack webhook](https://prosperstack.com/docs/webhooks/) that delivers events to a specified endpoint.\n\nSupported events are `flow_session_started` and `flow_session_completed`.\n\nA ProsperStack account can have a maximum of ten configured webhooks.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "events",
      "x-displayName": "Events",
      "description": "An event represents a ProsperStack event that occurred in your account. These are the same events that are delivered via configured webhooks.\n\nThe events endpoints can be used as an alternative or in addition to [webhooks](https://prosperstack.com/docs/webhooks/). Use the events endpoints if you would like to poll for new events rather than receiving them in real-time, or to catch up on any events a webhook endpoint may have missed.\n\nUse the event `id` property to determine if your application has handled the event before.\n\nNote that the events endpoints are only guaranteed to maintain event history for 30 days.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "customer_portal",
      "x-displayName": "Customer portal",
      "description": "The [customer portal](https://docs.prosperstack.com/customer-portal/enabling-the-customer-portal) allows customers to self-manage their subscriptions and billing details.\n\nCreating a portal session creates a unique URL for a specific customer. Create sessions via the API to seamlessly log customers in to the portal directly from your application or website.\n"
    }
  ],
  "paths": {
    "/events": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "List events",
        "operationId": "listEvents",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "after_id",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filter events occurring after the specified ID",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "event",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filter events by event type (`flow_session_started`, `flow_session_completed`)",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "created_at",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filter events by the `created_at` property. Specify as a dictionary with one or more of the following properties:\n\n- `created_at[gt]` \u2014 Return events where `created_at` is greater than this value\n- `created_at[lt]` \u2014 Return events where `created_at` is less than this value\n- `created_at[gte]` \u2014 Return events where `created_at` is greater than or equal to this value\n- `created_at[lte]` \u2014 Return events where `created_at` is less than or equal to this value\n\nSpecify date values in [ISO 8601](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601) format.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "cursor",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Pagination cursor to retrieve",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Limit of events to return",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "minimum": 1,
              "maximum": 100
            }
          }
        ],
        "tags": [
          "events"
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "OK",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "required": [
                    "data"
                  ],
                  "properties": {
                    "data": {
                      "type": "array",
                      "items": {
                        "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Event"
                      }
                    },
                    "next_cursor": {
                      "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Cursor"
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Unauthorized",
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Error"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/events/{id}": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "Retrieve an event",
        "operationId": "retrieveEventById",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "id",
            "in": "path",
            "description": "Event ID to retrieve",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "tags": [
          "events"
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "OK",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/Event"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Unauthorized",
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Error"
          },
          "404": {
            "description": "Not Found",
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Error"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/customer_portal/sessions": {
      "post": {
        "summary": "Create a customer portal session",
        "operationId": "createCustomerPortalSession",
        "tags": [
          "customer_portal"
        ],
        "requestBody": {
          "$ref": "#/components/requestBodies/CustomerPortalSession"
        },
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "description": "Created",
            "headers": {
              "Location": {
                "description": "The URL of the created customer portal session",
                "schema": {
                  "type": "string",
                  "format": "uri"
                }
              }
            },
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "$ref": "#/components/schemas/CustomerPortalSession"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "description": "Bad Request",
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Error"
          },
          "401": {
            "description": "Unauthorized",
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Error"
          },
          "409": {
            "description": "Conflict",
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Error"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/flows": {
      "get": {
        "summary": "List flows",
        "operationId": "listFlows",
